{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-sistent-component-js-content-file-path-src-collections-sistent-components-avatar-group-code-mdx","path":"/projects/sistent/components/avatar-group/code","result":{"data":{"mdx":{"body":"\nimport { Avatar, AvatarGroup } from \"@sistent/sistent\";\nimport user1 from \"../../../../assets/images/sistent/placeholder/user.webp\";\nimport user2 from \"../../../../assets/images/sistent/placeholder/user.webp\";\nimport user3 from \"../../../../assets/images/sistent/placeholder/user.webp\";\nimport user4 from \"../../../../assets/images/sistent/placeholder/user.webp\";\n\nThe AvatarGroup component helps visually group multiple avatars in a compact and meaningful layout, often representing users in a shared context.\n\n<h3>AvatarGroup Implementation Variants</h3>\n\n<h4>Basic AvatarGroup</h4>\nDisplay a horizontal group of avatars with default overlap.\n\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <div style={{ display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'center', width: '100%' }}>\n        <AvatarGroup>\n          <Avatar src={user1} alt=\"User 1\" />\n          <Avatar src={user2} alt=\"User 2\" />\n          <Avatar src={user3} alt=\"User 3\" />\n        </AvatarGroup>\n      </div>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"basic-group\" collapsible code={`<AvatarGroup>\n  <Avatar src=\"/user1.jpg\" alt=\"User 1\" />\n  <Avatar src=\"/user2.jpg\" alt=\"User 2\" />\n  <Avatar src=\"/user3.jpg\" alt=\"User 3\" />\n</AvatarGroup>`} />\n</div>\n\n<h4>Max Avatars</h4>\nLimit the number of visible avatars using the `max` prop.\n\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <div style={{ display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'center', width: '100%' }}>\n        <AvatarGroup max={3}>\n          <Avatar src={user1} alt=\"User 1\" />\n          <Avatar src={user2} alt=\"User 2\" />\n          <Avatar src={user3} alt=\"User 3\" />\n          <Avatar src={user4} alt=\"User 4\" />\n        </AvatarGroup>\n      </div>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"max-group\" collapsible code={`<AvatarGroup max={3}>\n  <Avatar src=\"/user1.jpg\" />\n  <Avatar src=\"/user2.jpg\" />\n  <Avatar src=\"/user3.jpg\" />\n  <Avatar src=\"/user4.jpg\" />\n</AvatarGroup>`} />\n</div>\n\n<h4>Custom Spacing</h4>\nControl the spacing between avatars.\n\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <div style={{ display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'center', width: '100%' }}>\n        <AvatarGroup spacing=\"medium\">\n          <Avatar src={user1} />\n          <Avatar src={user2} />\n          <Avatar src={user3} />\n        </AvatarGroup>\n      </div>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"spacing-group\" collapsible code={`<AvatarGroup spacing=\"medium\">\n  <Avatar src=\"/user1.jpg\" />\n  <Avatar src=\"/user2.jpg\" />\n  <Avatar src=\"/user3.jpg\" />\n</AvatarGroup>`} />\n</div>\n\n<h4>Shape Variants</h4>\nMix avatar shape variants like square and rounded.\n\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <div style={{ display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'center', width: '100%' }}>\n        <AvatarGroup>\n          <Avatar variant=\"rounded\" src={user1} />\n          <Avatar variant=\"square\" src={user2} />\n          <Avatar src={user3} />\n        </AvatarGroup>\n      </div>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"variant-group\" collapsible code={`<AvatarGroup>\n  <Avatar variant=\"rounded\" src=\"/user1.jpg\" />\n  <Avatar variant=\"square\" src=\"/user2.jpg\" />\n  <Avatar src=\"/user3.jpg\" />\n</AvatarGroup>`} />\n</div>\n\n<h4>Total Avatars</h4>\nYou can indicate the total number of avatars using the `total` prop, even if not all are rendered.\n\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <div style={{ display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'center', width: '100%' }}>\n        <AvatarGroup total={7}>\n          <Avatar src={user1} />\n          <Avatar src={user2} />\n          <Avatar src={user3} />\n        </AvatarGroup>\n      </div>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"total-avatars\" collapsible code={`<AvatarGroup total={7}>\n  <Avatar src=\"/user1.jpg\" />\n  <Avatar src=\"/user2.jpg\" />\n  <Avatar src=\"/user3.jpg\" />\n</AvatarGroup>`} />\n</div>\n\n<h4>Custom Surplus Renderer</h4>\nCustomize the overflow display using the `renderSurplus` prop for more control over surplus appearance.\n\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <div style={{ display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'center', width: '100%' }}>\n        <AvatarGroup\n          max={2}\n          renderSurplus={(surplus) => (\n            <span>+{surplus.toString()[0]}k</span>\n          )}\n          total={4251}\n        >\n          <Avatar src={user1} />\n          <Avatar src={user2} />\n          <Avatar src={user3} />\n          <Avatar src={user4} />\n        </AvatarGroup>\n      </div>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"custom-surplus\" collapsible code={`<AvatarGroup\n  max={2}\n  renderSurplus={(surplus) => (\n    <Avatar sx={{ bgcolor: 'secondary.main' }}>{\\`+\\${surplus} more\\`}</Avatar>\n  )}\n>\n  <Avatar src=\"/user1.jpg\" />\n  <Avatar src=\"/user2.jpg\" />\n  <Avatar src=\"/user3.jpg\" />\n  <Avatar src=\"/user4.jpg\" />\n</AvatarGroup>`} />\n</div>\n","frontmatter":{"title":"AvatarGroup Code","description":"Below are practical implementation examples of theAvatarGroup component, showcasing different configurations such as max user limit, spacing, variant styling, and accessibility-friendly usage. These examples are designed to help you apply AvatarGroup effectively across team or user-related interfaces."}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/projects/sistent/components/avatar-group/code","componentName":"avatar-group","availablePages":["code","guidance","overview"],"frontmatter":{"title":"AvatarGroup Code","component":"avatar-group","description":"Below are practical implementation examples of theAvatarGroup component, showcasing different configurations such as max user limit, spacing, variant styling, and accessibility-friendly usage. These examples are designed to help you apply AvatarGroup effectively across team or user-related interfaces."}}},"staticQueryHashes":["4152005505","934084603"],"slicesMap":{}}